5.6 Synergistic Aging (v4.0 Addition)

5.6.1 Rationale

Space environment combines:

· Radiation (GCR, SPE)
· Thermal cycling (diurnal)
· Mechanical stress (pressure, loads)

Testing these separately underestimates damage.

5.6.2 Test Protocol

Facility: In-situ ion irradiation + thermal cycling + tensile stage

Component Specification
Ion beam 3 MeV Au⁺⁺, variable flux
Temperature control -150°C to +500°C, cycling
Mechanical load Up to 500 MPa
Atmosphere Vacuum (10⁻⁷ Torr)
In-situ diagnostics Digital image correlation, electrical resistance

Test matrix:

· Radiation only (baseline)
· Thermal cycling only (baseline)
· Combined radiation + thermal cycling
· Combined radiation + thermal cycling + stress

5.6.3 Expected Outcomes

· Acceleration factors for crack growth
· Validation of AI synergistic aging models
· Identification of worst-case damage regimes

